# How to check the website locally?
In terminal
>> bundle exec jekyll serve    
Website can be open at 
http://localhost:4000   

if the bundle has not been installed, use following commands to install
>> brew install ruby
>> echo 'export PATH="/opt/homebrew/opt/ruby/bin:$PATH"' >> ~/.zshrc
>> source ~/.zshrc
>> gem install bundler jekyll
>> bundle install
